<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="create_validation_notification">
    <title>Create or edit a validation
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170111T132427+0100" comment="Sned via DHIS2 internal messaging system" flag="done"?>notification<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Validation</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Validation
                    notification</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T112410+0200" comment="Do not refer to the FAB as an icon, according to MS Manual of Style." flag="done"?>button<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Type a <emphasis role="bold"
                    ><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170110T171331+0100" comment="Unique name required?"?>Name<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select <emphasis role="bold"
                    ><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170111T151533+0100" comment="Verify order in UI" flag="done"?>Validation<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    rules</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Recipient user groups</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Select <emphasis role="bold">Notify users in hierarchy
                only</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>If you select this option, notifications are only send to users which are linked
                to organisation units which are either ancestors or children of the organisation
                unit associated with the validation
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170113T104010+0100" comment="Removed text:
&quot;
If you select this option, each user in the user group(s) will be alerted only for validation exceptions in an organisation unit to which the user has been assigned through user management -- or for any lower-level organisation unit under the assigned organisation unit. &quot;"?>violation<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            <para>If you don't select this option, each user in the assigned user group(s) will
                receive all validation violations send to the group, regardless of their assigned
                organisation units.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Create the <emphasis role="bold">Subject
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170113T102252+0100" comment="Pending example from SME."?>template<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
            <para>Double-click the parameters in the <emphasis role="bold">Template
                    variables</emphasis> field to add them to your subject.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Create the <emphasis role="bold">Message
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170113T102302+0100" comment="Pending example from SME."?>template<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
            <para>Double-click the parameter names in the <emphasis role="bold">Template
                    variables</emphasis> field to add them to your message.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>
